17 §1333. Accumulation of annual leave; conversion to membership service
18 A member shall be allowed to accumulate without limitation all of the
19 member's unused annual leave. When a member retires, or dies while still a member
20 of the fund and before retirement leaving a surviving spouse or dependent, or both,
21 who are entitled to benefits under this Chapter, his unused accumulated annual leave
22 which was earned under civil service the commission or administrative rules shall
23 be added to his membership service, the addition to membership service to be on the
24 basis of one work day for each eight hours of unused annual leave. Fractional days
25 of one-half day or more shall be counted as one day and fractional days of less than
26 one-half day shall be disregarded. The member's unused annual leave shall not be
27 used to determine eligibility for retirement, but shall be credited to the member only
28 after it is determined that the member is otherwise eligible for retirement.
